      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i need help writing a rejection email for a candidate. they made it to the final round for a senior dev role here in austin but we decided to go with someone else. they were actually really good and had great technical skills, so i want the email to be professional and kind but still clear that we aren't moving forward. can u help me draft something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can help you draft a rejection email that's both professional and kind. Here's a sample:\n\n\"Dear [Candidate Name],\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the status of your application for the Senior Developer position at [Company Name]. We were impressed by your exceptional technical skills and experience, and I'm grateful for the time you took to interview with us. After careful consideration, we've decided to move forward with another candidate whose skills and fit for the role align more closely with our current needs.\n\nPlease know that this decision is in no way a reflection on your abilities or potential as a developer. We appreciate the interest you showed in our company and wish you the best of luck in your ongoing job search.\n\nThank you again for your interest in [Company Name], and we wish you continued success in your career.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\"\n\nThis email aims to be kind and appreciative of the candidate's skills while still being clear and direct about the decision. You can adjust it to fit your company's tone and style.",
