      "content": "Here's a revised version with a bit more warmth and a nod to the difficulty of the decision:\n\n\"Dear [Candidate Name],\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the status of your application for the Senior Developer position at [Company Name]. I want to start by expressing my sincere gratitude for the time and effort you invested in our interview process. Your technical expertise and passion for software development truly shone through, and we were impressed by your ability to tackle complex problems with ease.\n\nAfter careful consideration, I regret to inform you that we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose skills and experience align more closely with the specific needs of our team at this time. Please know that this decision was not made lightly, and it was a difficult choice given the exceptional caliber of candidates we've received.\n\nI want to assure you that we were thoroughly impressed by your skills and experience, and we have no doubt that you will find a role that is a great fit for you. We appreciate the interest you showed in [Company Name] and wish you continued success in your career.\n\nThank you again for your interest in our company, and we wish you all the best in your ongoing job search.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\"\n\nThis version aims",
